name: 汉娜·泽特博格
name_full: 汉娜·泽特博格 Hanna Zetterberg
introduction: Rebecca Hanna Zetterberg Struwe (born 15 February 1973 in Skarpnäck) is a Swedish actress and politician of the Left Party.At the age of eleven years, she played the lead role in the film adaptation of Astrid Lindgren's Ronja. It was their only film role. With 21 years Zetterberg was elected to the Swedish Parliament and represented from 1994 to 1998 as deputy of the Left Party's interests.Zetterberg is a Swedish journalist and television presenter Philip married Struve, with whom she has two children. She lives in Stockholm. End of February 2011 the couple filed for divorce in the Tingsrätt. Since September 2010 Hanna Zetterberg lives at another address. [1] Since the couple has children, the divorce is final under Swedish law after six months.
